<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211/2128: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Governor of Illinois</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Emmerson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Springfield</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-07">July 7, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received 8:52
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Castle. Your telegram relative to arrest of Mexican Consul at Chicago
                            on chargé of contempt of court of Judge Thomas Green received. We are
                            making an immediate investigation to see what can be done and will
                            advise you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Louis L.
                            Emmerson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>